## Code navigation: use `ams`, not Read/Grep, for structure

This project is indexed by `ams` (AI Module Signatures): compact symbol
signatures with exact line spans instead of full file reads. One `describe`
costs 10–40× fewer tokens than reading the file. The index self-heals on
every query — never stale, no rebuild step.

Setup once per session: `which ams` (install:
`curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/StMalina/ams/main/install.sh | sh`);
if the project has no `.ams/` yet, run `ams build` at the root.

### The 3 commands that cover 90% of navigation

1. **Orient in a directory** — `ams tree [dir]` (instead of Glob + Reads):
   ```
   src/auth.ts   ts   820 loc  api:8   used-by:12   jwt,redis
   ```
   High `api` + high `used-by` = hub file, start there.

2. **See inside a file** — `ams describe <file>` (instead of Read):
   ```
   src/auth.ts [820 loc, ts, used-by:12]
     function validateToken(token: string): User | null  @42-78 exported
     class AuthService  @97-410 exported
   ```

3. **Read only the body you need** — `@103-160` → read the file with
   offset=103, limit=58. Never read a whole file when you have its spans.

### Before changing any exported API

- `ams related <file>` — deps + reverse deps (`used-by`): what breaks.
- `ams refs <name>` — usage sites, `calls 12, 45 | value 88` (`value` =
  passed as handler/callback, e.g. router registrations). Common names
  collapse to per-file counts — narrow with `--in <dir>`. Dynamic dispatch
  and string-based lookups are not indexed — fall back to grep if in doubt.
- `ams find <name>` — where a symbol is defined (substring, exact spans).
- `ams search <words>` — full-text over names/signatures/docstrings when the
  exact name is unknown (camelCase word-split, prefix match, any language).

### Rarely needed

When writing a new function, give it a one-line docstring/doc-comment (the
*why*, not a restatement of the signature) — it gets indexed for free.
For code you should NOT edit (legacy, third-party), use
`ams annotate <file>:<Symbol.path> "note"` — an out-of-band insight that
survives reindexing and is flagged `[stale]` when the body changes.
Flags: `--exported`, `--kind`, `--json`; `ams build --force` after a binary
upgrade.

**Not a grep replacement:** strings, log lines, config values → still
`rg`/`grep`. Supported languages: TypeScript/TSX, JavaScript/JSX
(ESM+CommonJS), Rust, Python, Go, PHP, Java, Kotlin, C#, Ruby.
